<ul id="commtree_64715178"><li id="tree_64715192" class="comment full contain"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_64715192" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64715192" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64715192" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64715192" name="comment_link_64715192" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23425710&amp;cid=64715192" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64715192)" >Re:You don't help your case...</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64715192" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64715192); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Rei">Rei</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Rei">( 128717 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64715192">		
		on Sunday August 18, 2024 @04:54AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23425710&amp;cid=64715192">#64715192</a>)
		<small><a href="http://atashi2.eaku.net/" title="http://atashi2.eaku.net/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64715192"><p>Just to elaborate more on China, from the above BMJ article:</p><blockquote><div><p>An initial report from a WHO team sent to Wuhan struck many observers as premature in stating that a laboratory leak origin was &ldquo;extremely unlikely.&rdquo;2 That conclusion was criticised by WHO&rsquo;s director general, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, who said on 15 July that there had been a &ldquo;premature push&rdquo; to rule out the leak theory.</p><p>&ldquo;I was a lab technician myself, I&rsquo;m an immunologist, and I have worked in the lab, and lab accidents happen,&rdquo; Tedros said. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s common.&rdquo; He told reporters that WHO was &ldquo;asking China to be transparent, open and to cooperate, especially on the information, [the] raw data that we asked for in the early days of the pandemic.&rdquo;</p><p>Records of meetings at the Geneva agency in the pandemic&rsquo;s first days, obtained by the Associated Press last year, suggest that WHO leaders&rsquo; early praise of Chinese transparency was an effort to coax more information from the regime, while among themselves they expressed frustration at its secrecy.</p><p>Emergencies director Michael Ryan, who leads WHO&rsquo;s covid-19 response, privately compared China&rsquo;s behaviour unfavourably to the Democratic Republic of Congo&rsquo;s transparency over Ebola virus disease and noted that China had also delayed the release of vital information during the outbreak of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) in 2003.3</p><p>China&rsquo;s government initially hoped that the pandemic would boost China&rsquo;s reputation as it provided the developing world with cheap vaccines and showcased its own tight infection control. But a recent poll in several countries showed that China&rsquo;s public image has taken a hit.4 Chinese vaccines, meanwhile, have been troubled by slow deliveries and limited efficacy.</p><p>A Chinese official last week dismissed WHO&rsquo;s plan for a second phase to its Wuhan investigation. &ldquo;It is impossible for us to accept such an origin tracing plan,&rdquo; said Zeng Yixin, the vice minister of the National Health Commission, suggesting that WHO should instead investigate the United States. China&rsquo;s government has lent support to a conspiracy theory that blames the pandemic on the US military.5</p><p>&ldquo;Their position is irresponsible and, frankly, dangerous,&rdquo; the White House said in response. &ldquo;This is about saving lives in the future, and it&rsquo;s not a time to be stonewalling.&rdquo;</p></div></blockquote></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64715192">
